    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Bronze aerophones of the Celts dating from early second century BCE shaped like long trumpets and held vertically, with a bell styled in the form of an animal head: often a boar's head or a dragon.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
